<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3031] Groovy Console: binding is not preserved between selection invocations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3031</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems like there is a minor regression in GroovyConsole.&lt;br/&gt;
In previous versions it was possible to run several pieces of code, and binging variables were preserved between invocations.&lt;br/&gt;
Now binding seams to be empty for each next invocation. &lt;br/&gt;
I tried using snapshot 20080906095551.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
open groovyConsole, and paste this script:&lt;br/&gt;
x = 1&lt;br/&gt;
println x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Select and execute first line, then select and execute second line.&lt;br/&gt;
You will get groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException.&lt;br/&gt;
Full stack trace is attached: stacktrace.txt&lt;br/&gt;
In all previous GroovyConsole versions you would get &quot;1&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
