                            <comment id="14465318" author="shemnon" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2008 21:56:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was a side effect of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2958&quot; title=&quot;GroovyConsole does not execute GroovyTestCase subclasses as command line invocation does&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-2958&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-2958&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, GroovyShell.run does not respect the scriptness of the script.  i.e. it goes straight for the main method instead of instantiating it as a script if possible and setting the bindings and running via &apos;run&apos;.  So the fix went into GroovyShell..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
